org.jcvi.jillion.trace.sff

Interface SffParser

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    SffFileParser

    public interface SffParser
    SffParser is an interface that will parse a SFF formatted structure and call the appropriate visit methods on the given SffVisitor.
    Author:
    dkatzel

    • Method Summary

    • Method Detail

      • canParse

        boolean canParse()
        Can this handler accept new parse requests via parse() calls. Some implementations of SffParser may only allow one parse call in its lifetime (for example, if the sff structure is being parsed via an InputStream).
        Returns:
        true if this handler can handle new visit requests; false otherwise.

      • parse

        void parse(SffVisitor visitor)
    throws IOException
        Parse the sff structure and call the visit methods on the given visitor.
        Parameters:
        visitor - the visitor to call the visit methods on.
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is a problem parsing the file.
        NullPointerException - if visitor is null.
        IllegalStateException - if this handler can not accept any new parse requests.
        See Also:
        canParse()

      • parse

        void parse(SffVisitor visitor,
           SffVisitorCallback.SffVisitorMemento memento)
    throws IOException
        Parse the sff structure starting from the portion specified by the given SffVisitorCallback.SffVisitorMemento. and call the visit methods on the given visitor.
        Parameters:
        visitor - the visitor to call the visit methods on.
        memento - the SffVisitorCallback.SffVisitorMemento instance which will tell the parser where to start parsing. Only SffVisitorCallback.SffVisitorMementos generated by this parser instance are valid.
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is a problem parsing the file.
        NullPointerException - if visitor is null.
        UnsupportedOperationException - if this parser was created with an InputStream instead of a File.
        IllegalStateException - if this handler can not accept any new parse requests.
        See Also:
        canParse()
